      • calcWeightOfPoint

        public double calcWeightOfPoint(Point p)
        Returns value of given point calculated by barycentric coordinates. The point must be inside of triangle to calculate weight. If the point is outside of triangle method return NaN.
        Parameters:
        p - Weight of Point to calculate
        Returns:
        weight of point or NaN
        See Also:
        Triangle#calculatebarycentricWeights(utils.Point)

      • isPointOnTriangleSide

        public boolean isPointOnTriangleSide(Point p)
        Returns true if point is on some of the lines between triangles vertexes. That is, if one of the calculated brycentrinc weights is 0.
        Parameters:
        p - Point to check
        Returns:
        true if point is on triangles side

      • isValidDelaunay

        public boolean isValidDelaunay(MyArrayList<Point> listOfPoints)
        Checks if this triangle is a valid Delaunay triangle. That is if inside triangles circumcenter circle is not any other points that the triangles vertexes.
        Parameters:
        listOfPoints - list of points used in triangulation.
        Returns:
        true if triangle is a valid Delaunay triangle

      • findCircumcenter

        public Point findCircumcenter()
        Returns triangle's circumcenter, that is the point where the distance to all the vertices is same. Steps how to calculate the cirumcenter:
        • Create line AB from vertex1 to vertex2 and line BC vertex2 to vertex3
        • Find midpoints for those lines
        • Find normals for lines AB and BC by their midpoints
        • Find intersect point from previous step's lines
        Returns:

      • getCircumcenterCircle

        public Circle getCircumcenterCircle()
        Returns circle representing triangle's circumcenter.
        Returns:
        Circle of circumcenter or null if all vrtexes are on same line.
